    "content": "{\"aspect_ratio\":\"4:5\",\"prompt\":\"Create a clean Portuguese troubleshooting infographic for a Windows + smartphone setup. Theme: network/app support guide. Title at the top: \\\"WO Mic вҖ” Erro: UDP port is occupied\\\". Visual style: modern tech infographic, dark background with blue/cyan accents, high contrast, clean icons, easy to read, organized in clear blocks and arrows like a system diagram. Use a structured layout with sections labeled \\\"FATO\\\", \\\"CAUSA\\\", and \\\"CORREГҮГғO\\\".\\n\\nContent to include:\\n\\nBlock 1 вҖ” \\\"FATO\\\"\\nText: \\\"O erro \\\\\\\"UDP port is occupied\\\\\\\" significa que a porta de rede usada pelo WO Mic jГЎ estГЎ ocupada no Windows.\\\"\\n\\nBlock 2 вҖ” \\\"CAUSA\\\"\\nText: \\\"Isso geralmente acontece quando o prГіprio WO Mic ficou aberto em segundo plano ou travou, mantendo a porta presa.\\\"\\nInclude a small visual flow: \\\"WO Mic travado / em segundo plano\\\" вҶ’ \\\"porta UDP ocupada\\\" вҶ’ \\\"falha ao conectar\\\".\\n\\nBlock 3 вҖ” \\\"CORREГҮГғO\\\"\\nShow a numbered checklist with icons:\\n1. \\\"Feche o WO Mic no PC e no celular.\\\"\\n2. \\\"Abra o Gerenciador de Tarefas com Ctrl + Shift + Esc.\\\"\\n3. \\\"Procure por WOMicClient.exe.\\\"\\n4. \\\"Finalize o processo.\\\"\\n5. \\\"Abra o WO Mic novamente e tente conectar.\\\"\\n\\nBlock 4 вҖ” \\\"SE CONTINUAR DANDO ERRO\\\"\\nText: \\\"Altere a porta no PC e no celular para o mesmo nГәmero, por exemplo 8130.\\\"\\nThen show two side-by-side mini panels:\\nLeft panel title: \\\"No PC\\\"\\nText: \\\"Options > Advanced > Media Port > 8130\\\"\\nRight panel title: \\\"No celular\\\"\\nText: \\\"ConfiguraГ§Гөes > Port > 8130\\\"\\n\\nFinal highlighted note at the bottom:\\n\\\"A porta precisa ser igual nos dois dispositivos.\\\"\\n\\nUse clear typography in Portuguese, accurate spelling, crisp UI-like cards, and small icons representing PC, smartphone, task manager, process, and network port. Do not include any brand logos or watermarks. The result should look like a polished YouTube/community post or support-card graphic.\"}",
